    "content": "<p>In the given circuit, for maximum power to be delivered to R<sub>L</sub>, its value should be ______&nbsp;Ω. (Round off to 2 decimal places.)</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lb0gadpe/82ba9345-604b-4aa4-b51a-f8d1e05e2fb4/b1deec20-6eeb-11ed-af30-015f7c535d24/file-1lb0gadpf.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lb0gadpe/82ba9345-604b-4aa4-b51a-f8d1e05e2fb4/b1deec20-6eeb-11ed-af30-015f7c535d24/file-1lb0gadpf.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Electric Circuits - Network Theorems Question 5 English\"></p>\n",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "1.40TO1.42",
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { Given circuit is as shown below, } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh5znj9p/2367e304-327b-44e3-9419-bf9c64321d75/6e4d7fd0-b178-11f0-a8fc-1beb57a635e8/file-jaoe38c1mh5znj9q.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh5znj9p/2367e304-327b-44e3-9419-bf9c64321d75/6e4d7fd0-b178-11f0-a8fc-1beb57a635e8/file-jaoe38c1mh5znj9q.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Electric Circuits - Network Theorems Question 5 English Explanation\">$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; Z_{t h}=\\frac{2 \\times j 2}{2+j 2} \\\\ &amp; \\left|Z_{t h}\\right|=\\frac{2 \\times j 2}{\\sqrt{2^2+2^2}}=\\frac{4}{2 \\sqrt{2}}=\\sqrt{2} \\Omega \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>For maximum power transfer,</p>\n<p>$$ R_L=\\left|Z_{t h}\\right|=\\sqrt{2}=1.414 \\Omega $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct answer is 1.414 .</p>",
