    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>For the circuit shown, if $$i = \\sin 1000t$$, the instantaneous value of the Thevenin's equivalent voltage (in Volts) across the terminals a-b at time t = 5 ms is __________ (Round off to 2 decimal places).</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz2v42f2/55ac8075-0964-452d-8338-e43ce5a76971/6da13930-4b64-11ef-842e-2ba19c3c5992/file-jaoe38c1lz2v42f8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz2v42f2/55ac8075-0964-452d-8338-e43ce5a76971/6da13930-4b64-11ef-842e-2ba19c3c5992/file-jaoe38c1lz2v42f8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2023 Electric Circuits - Network Theorems Question 3 English\"></p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "-12.1TO-11.9",
    "explanation": "<p>Given circuit is shown below,</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz2v7i2f/ab8c0348-a50e-43c3-ad06-3eab94105cf9/cd248470-4b64-11ef-8b23-cd381defbfce/file-jaoe38c1lz2v7i2g.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz2v7i2f/ab8c0348-a50e-43c3-ad06-3eab94105cf9/cd248470-4b64-11ef-8b23-cd381defbfce/file-jaoe38c1lz2v7i2g.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2023 Electric Circuits - Network Theorems Question 3 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<p>By source transformation,</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz2v93xg/c373dfbd-3214-4cc1-9836-f22c3c29b667/f9d6ee40-4b64-11ef-8b23-cd381defbfce/file-jaoe38c1lz2v93xh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz2v93xg/c373dfbd-3214-4cc1-9836-f22c3c29b667/f9d6ee40-4b64-11ef-8b23-cd381defbfce/file-jaoe38c1lz2v93xh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2023 Electric Circuits - Network Theorems Question 3 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>$$ V_{t h}=i_x(10-10 j) $$</p>\n\n<p>By KVL in loop,</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; (10+10 j) \\sin 1000 t+(10+j 10) i_x-4 i_x+(10-j 10) i_x=0 \\\\\\\\ &amp; i_x=\\frac{(10+j 10) \\sin 1000 t}{16} \\\\\\\\ &amp; V_{t h}=(10-j 10) i_x \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; V_{t h}=\\frac{(10-j 10)(10+j 10) \\sin 1000 t}{16} \\\\\\\\ &amp; V_{t h}=\\frac{100+100}{16} \\sin 1000 t \\\\\\\\ &amp; V_{t h}=12.5 \\sin 1000 t \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\mathrm{At} t=5 \\mathrm{msec}, \\\\\\\\ &amp; V_{t h}=12.5 \\sin 5 \\\\\\\\ &amp; V_{t h}=-11.98 \\mathrm{~V} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct answer is -11.98 .</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
