    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { Calculation of } V_{\\text {th }} \\text { : } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh65ml3i/e7626734-9ca2-47e9-b0c5-7131285969cf/caae36e0-b18f-11f0-9ec5-a735814724b3/file-jaoe38c1mh65ml3j.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh65ml3i/e7626734-9ca2-47e9-b0c5-7131285969cf/caae36e0-b18f-11f0-9ec5-a735814724b3/file-jaoe38c1mh65ml3j.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Electric Circuits - Network Theorems Question 4 English Explanation 1\">From the circuit diagram,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; i=5 \\mathrm{~A} \\\\ &amp; V_{t h}=3 i+10 i=13 i \\\\ &amp; V_{t h}=65 \\mathrm{~V} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Calculation of $\\boldsymbol{R}_{\\text {th }}$ :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh65mlxd/24a6dd53-dbd8-4d71-87f0-ef90c445feac/cb523f10-b18f-11f0-9ec5-a735814724b3/file-jaoe38c1mh65mlxe.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh65mlxd/24a6dd53-dbd8-4d71-87f0-ef90c445feac/cb523f10-b18f-11f0-9ec5-a735814724b3/file-jaoe38c1mh65mlxe.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Electric Circuits - Network Theorems Question 4 English Explanation 2\">From the circuit diagram,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; i=I_{d c} \\\\ &amp; V_{d c}=2 I_{d c}+3 i+10 i \\\\ &amp; V_{d c}=2 I_{d c}+3 I_{d c}+10 I_{d c} \\\\ &amp; \\frac{V_{d c}}{I_{d c}}=15 \\Omega \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (C).</p>",
